# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# convergence loop (raw 38 implement-omega-converge — applies to
# every entry above; recorded here once for reference)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Pick the smallest blocked entry (lowest SH#) whose blockers are
#    cleared. If multiple eligible, pick lowest acceptance-bar.
# 2. Execute the next un-attempted phase listed under `attempts`.
# 3. Bench the witness target(s) under quiet load (load avg <2).
# 4. Append result to `attempts` log with date + measurement +
#    `next:` line pointing to the subsequent phase OR the
#    omega-stop reached.
# 5. If the entry's `omega-stop` witness is reached, flip status
#    done (or partial if a sub-scope is closed but the entry's
#    full acceptance is not).
# 6. If a hard blocker emerges that the omega-stop cannot resolve,
#    record `omega-saturation-exempt <reason>` with explicit
#    enforce-layer-rationale.
# 7. Iterate until SH-Ω fixpoint.
#
# Don't-touch (parallel-agent settled territory; carry-over):
#   - self/runtime.c              (perf-32 settled)
#   - build/hexa_interp shim      (Agent 2 settled)
#   - self/native/hexa_cc.c L1    (Agent 4 setenv)
#   - hive/, anima/, nexus/       (read-only)
# self/main.hexa is touchable but coordinate with Agent 3's layered
# cache (132d1e17) — every wedge that enters aot_build_slot must
# preserve the flatten/transpile/link cache key invariants.
#
# Build cycle:
#   hexa build self/main.hexa <out>         → build/artifacts/app
#   cp build/artifacts/app /Users/ghost/core/hexa-lang/hexa
#   codesign --sign - --force /Users/ghost/core/hexa-lang/hexa
# (omit codesign and macOS Gatekeeper SIGKILLs the second invoke.)
#
# .roadmap is uchg-locked. To edit:
#   chflags nouchg .roadmap && <edit> && chflags uchg .roadmap

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# engine-readable canonical entries (raw 37 plan-omega-saturation
# parser scope: `<family> <id> <status> "<name>"` + indented fields).
# Bullet sections above remain the human-authoritative source —
# these are duals consumed by tool/plan_omega_saturation_lint.hexa.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

